{
  "doc_id": "56318",
  "text": "Technical developments of the past [CITATION_1] years have contributed significantly to automated karyotyping, and there now are more than ten companies producing systems for computer processing of digitized chromosome images. These systems range from those that can only be described as \"electronic scissors\" to systems that combine metaphase finding as well as pattern classification of banded chromosomes to achieve a result that requires a minimum of human interaction.",
